tags: Treatment satisfaction,
review: It is easy to get an appointment in an emergency situation and the receptionist was empathetic to the waiting patients. The doctors are knowledgeable and can correlate a problem with the patient as an individual. The team of paramedics supports the patient and facilitates the procedures efficiently. The toilet was clean and useable. The clinic has positive vibes for the well being of all and does not aggressively sell their own agenda to the patient.
She is excellent in every way from listening my problem to explaining the issue. Her behaviour is most comforting for a patient.

tags: Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,
review: Visited the doctor for the pregnancy before pregnancy till 8th month. However, ****** *** **** ** ********* *** *********** She diagnosed my wife with Pre-Term delivery and advised immediate admission into recommended hospital ***** *** ***** ******* *********. She even didn't gave time for ultrasound. However, we took the chances and did ultrasound  and everything was fine. ** **** *** ********* ******* **** ******** ******* *** ** *** **** ********* *** **** *********. ******* *** ** *** ******* ** ***** ******** *** ****** ********* ** ********* *** *** ******* ********
reply_text: Thanks for your feedback.sometimes it is very difficult to ascertain whether it is a preterm labour or gastritis specially when the symptoms are very similar .Being the treating doctor from the beginning it was my duty to prevent any complications for which you were advised admission for observation and further management .The ultrasound and all required investigations are usually done in the hospital and then only course of action is decided.you were always accommodated inspite of the arguments you indulged into with the clinic staff just because you had to wait for your turn.all the best.

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,
review:
First I met Dr. Harveen for PCOS treatment & on the very first visit, I felt comfortable.  She didn't only prescribe medicines but also give good advice & motivation to have a good lifestyle & diet. After that when we planned for a child, she guided us in the whole journey.
The way she handled me throughout the pregnancy was too good. I got panic & take stress too easily but the way she listens to me patiently & guide me cure everything. She is very polite & we feel a homely vibe with her, always reachable. There were few complications in my pregnancy but the trust we have in her took everything smoothly.

tags: Doctor friendliness,Treatment satisfaction,Explanation of the health issue,

review:
I visited Dr Harveen Kaur in 2017 for my UTI issues, she was very polite and helped me to understand my health issue , also provided correct medication to solve my problem

After it got cured we wanted to have a child, so she guided us entirely in this whole journey from the initial checkups to final delivery

We had so much trust in her that we decided to have our baby in Delhi itself and not in our hometown, since we had developed a great relationship with her

review: We had a good experience. Docter listened  our problem patiently and gave a good piece of advice. And also suggest to take second opinion as well.
After visiting doctor, I was said to have certain tests and they will share the results/bill on WhatsApp. Now the staff is no more responsive on WhatsApp and neither the doctor.
reply_text: Thanks for taking out time to write this feedback but somethings need to be clarified,firstly all your reports were mailed to you in a pdf form and for your convenience when you forwarded these reports to the doctor you were informed by the doctor that the reports were normal.Secondly none of the staff or the doctor is supposed to send the bills on what's app,they have to be collected from the clinic on the same day or on  your next visit .Most importantly being a pregnant patient your focus should be more on the treatment part rather than taking stress about  receiving bills on what's app.
